":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"130268","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/130268/ba8fad33-b57e-4cb7-a9a8-ba2cbced918c.png"},{"n":"Patrick Neil Bentley","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":122,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"39736"}],"female_count":0,"male_count":5,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":1,"inc_elected":1,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":0},{"ward":"Bushbury North","seats":1,"turnout_pct":35.91,"results_url":"https://www.wolverhampton.gov.uk/your-council-and-meetings/elections-and-voting/local-elections-2026","candidates":[{"n":"Susan Lawrence","p":"Reform UK","v":1365,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"130335","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/130335/2d20a98d-5ea3-463c-a6c6-260601692711.png"},{"n":"Andrew William McNeil","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":713,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"17834","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/17834-28a59bb0-831c-4550-af1c-2e7dadddbbd4.png","tw":"\"McEnglish\""},{"n":"Gary Edwards","p":"Labour Party","v":658,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"96382","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/96382/2c8055a7-8025-4466-9fe7-2316dee1a39c.png","bd":"1969"},{"n":"Sarabjit Singh","p":"Green Party","v":438,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"low","pid":"130336"},{"n":"Ann Jenkins","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":143,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"17846"}],"female_count":2,"male_count":3,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Bushbury South & Low Hill","seats":1,"turnout_pct":24.34,"results_url":"https://www.wolverhampton.gov.uk/your-council-and-meetings/elections-and-voting/local-elections-2026","candidates":[{"n":"Armin Berenjian","p":"Reform UK","v":921,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"126611","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/126611/308ea933-a6ea-4ba1-89f3-5fdb162f2199.png","stmt":"Dear Residents,\n\nMy name is Dr Armin Berenjian. I am a Chartered Civil and Structural Engineer, an Associate at AtkinsRéalis, and a proud resident of Bushbury.\n\nI bring real expertise; a PhD. in Structural Engineering and years of delivering major projects across the UK.\n\nI specialise in building safety, quality, and getting the job done properly, on time, and on budget.\n\nLet’s be honest: Labour-led Wolverhampton has been an absolute letdown!\n\nWe see it everywhere - projects delayed, millions overspent, and work that simply isn’t good enough. Roads are repaired only to fail again weeks later.\n\nIn Bushbury South and Low Hill, residents are fed up with potholes, poor workmanship, and council housing repairs that are ignored or badly carried out.\n\nIt doesn’t stop there. The list goes on like Wolverhampton Market, Bilston Market, Beatties, Cycle Lanes, the Civic Hall - too many projects plagued by delay, waste, and substandard delivery.\n\nThis is not acceptable!\n\nOur city deserves competence. It deserves accountability. It deserves leadership that understands how to deliver, not one excuse after the other.\n\nI will bring a professional, no-nonsense approach to the council. I will challenge failure wherever it exists - be it past, present, or future failures. I will stand up for taxpayers who are tired of seeing their money wasted.\n\nI am stepping forward because I care deeply about where we live and  because our city can no longer afford more of the same because it’s time to raise standards and restore pride in Wolverhampton.\n\nIt’s time for a shake-up.\nIt’s time for real accountability.\nIt’s time for Reform.","li":"\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/armin-berenjian/\"","bd":"1989"},{"n":"Paul Ian Brookfield","p":"Labour Party","v":756,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","inc":true,"pid":"108893","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/108893/8f96c46f-b1b3-43d1-b435-b143d13e2521.png"},{"n":"Cade George Hatton","p":"Green Party","v":362,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"130266"},{"n":"Anthony Charles Gething","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":219,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"93720"},{"n":"Shane P Slater","p":"Independent","v":81,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"130267","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/130267/cb706052-f636-4f2e-9c53-218bcbe98cf3.png","stmt":"I am standing as an independent candidate for Bushbury South and Low Hill because our community deserves a strong, honest voice that answers to residents—not to a political party.\n\nThis area has been overlooked for too long. We see it in the condition of our roads, the lack of investment in local services, concerns around safety, and the feeling that decisions are made without properly listening to the people who live here.\n\nMy priority is simple: to put Bushbury South and Low Hill first. I will work to improve neighbourhood safety, push for cleaner streets and better-maintained public spaces, and fight for the investment our community deserves. I will be accessible, accountable, and transparent in every decision I make.\n\nAs an independent, I am free to focus on what truly matters—your concerns, your priorities, and the future of our community. No party politics. Just real action and real representation.\n\nThis is our community. It’s time it had a voice that truly represents it."}],"female_count":0,"male_count":5,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":1,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":1,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"East Park","seats":1,"turnout_pct":28.26,"results_url":"https://www.wolverhampton.gov.uk/your-council-and-meetings/elections-and-voting/local-elections-2026","candidates":[{"n":"Dave Evans","p":"Reform UK","v":1029,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"130138","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/130138/8079bf27-19dc-4238-8bf1-392c5df1d7a1.png"},{"n":"Louise Margaret Miles","p":"Labour Party","v":868,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"17871","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/17871/a6f60e46-4181-4337-b472-9d121c3ddb39.png"},{"n":"Taliesin Quinn Damien Edwards","p":"Green Party","v":368,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"130137"},{"n":"Joe Stepien","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":240,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"96094"},{"n":"Steve Hall","p":"Independent","v":82,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"17272","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/17272/58442349-df56-452c-af01-01b9393f8a8c.png"}],"female_count":1,"male_count":4,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Ettingshall North","seats":1,"turnout_pct":27.52,"results_url":"https://www.wolverhampton.gov.uk/your-council-and-meetings/elections-and-voting/local-elections-2026","candidates":[{"n":"Jeszemma Rose Howl","p":"Labour Party","v":1032,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","inc":true,"pid":"95533","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/95533/91df8b1e-8602-46cc-a256-4f3ffedd48f9.png","stmt":"I’m delighted to be selected as the Labour Party candidate for my area, Ettingshall North.\n\nI live and work here with my family, and to be selected to represent my own area is a huge honour.\n\nI now work for a national charity, but I’ve spent many years working in early years and community work and have a real passion to make things better for the children and families of this area.  \n\nI’m a big believer in communities working together, and I know this area has a huge resource in its residents, our community needs a strong voice to advocate for it. \n\nI’m not shy of hard work, standing up for what is right and I’m always ready to listen."},{"n":"Manpreet Singh","p":"Green Party","v":665,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"low","pid":"129943"},{"n":"Gareth Walker","p":"Reform UK","v":644,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129944","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/129944/9fba7367-9231-429b-a63f-7fca28253deb.png"},{"n":"Surrinder Kumar Ram","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":228,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"96502"},{"n":"Tracy Cooper","p":"Independent","v":82,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"110986"}],"female_count":2,"male_count":3,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":1,"inc_elected":1,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":0},{"ward":"Ettingshall South & Spring Vale","seats":1,"turnout_pct":35.92,"results_url":"https://www.wolverhampton.gov.uk/your-council-and-meetings/elections-and-voting/local-elections-2026","candidates":[{"n":"Rob Greenway","p":"Reform UK","v":1632,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"130196","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/130196/9f3cd184-d4ab-4437-bf4a-5e0d213733df.png"},{"n":"Jasbinder Dehar","p":"Labour and Co-operative Party","v":1020,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","inc":true,"pid":"35774","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/35774/67748afd-d394-47ed-bd23-f504ac9ada3d.png","tw":"\"CllrJasDehar\""},{"n":"Siân Kumar","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":423,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"61370","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/61370-693016ee-581d-4760-bc69-cf04f13c59ca.png","tw":"\"Sian_Kumar\"","bd":"1992"},{"n":"Manish Kumar","p":"Green Party","v":382,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"130197"}],"female_count":2,"male_count":2,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":1,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":1,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Fallings Park","seats":1,"turnout_pct":32.27,"results_url":"https://www.wolverhampton.gov.uk/your-council-and-meetings/elections-and-voting/local-elections-2026","candidates":[{"n":"Stu Goldsmith","p":"Reform UK","v":1230,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"129931"},{"n":"Chris Burden","p":"Labour and Co-operative Party","v":842,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","inc":true,"pid":"129930","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/129930/5426128b-5e74-41a8-ad3b-830072d1ed64.png"},{"n":"Julia Dickens","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":416,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"95566","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/95566/b2984942-1058-493e-bbb9-bf7e99ec922a.png"},{"n":"Tony Wortley","p":"Green Party","v":300,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"129932","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/129932/3fea0ed9-65ac-4d80-8f29-58b30cfc6cce.png"},{"n":"Peter Nixon","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":152,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"17857"}],"female_count":1,"male_count":4,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":1,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":1,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Graiseley","seats":1,"turnout_pct":34.49,"results_url":"https://www.wolverhampton.gov.uk/your-council-and-meetings/elections-and-voting/local-elections-2026","candidates":[{"n":"Gurbax Kaur","p":"Labour Party","v":1126,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"124677","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/124677/2d31107f-ac3a-4ad1-b480-611c5776ce9b.png"},{"n":"Suki Bains","p":"Green Party","v":676,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"95571"},{"n":"Sarp Dayanik","p":"Reform UK","v":661,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"129509","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/129509/1cec7df2-a912-47f0-a18f-12de7951c97f.png","stmt":"My name is Sarp Dayanik, and I am standing to represent Graiseley Ward.\n\nWith decades of expertise in managing projects and budgets, I’m committed to ensuring that our local government acts responsibly and prioritizes community needs. My focus is on transparent finance and practical solutions that benefit everyone. Join me in making Graiseley a better place.\n\nWolverhampton has been my home for over 40 years.\n\nI graduated from Wolverhampton Polytechnic with a degree in Computer Science, and I come not as a career politician but as someone rooted in the real world.\n\nI have spent four decades in business and construction. This experience has taught me how to manage budgets, deliver results, and hold people to account. These are skills that are urgently needed in our council today.\n\nWolverhampton is now carrying nearly £1 billion in debt.\n\nResidents rightly expect better services, yet too much of our money is being swallowed by interest payments over £30 Million a year rather than invested in our roads, neighbourhoods, and public services.\n\nAcross Graiseley, the signs of decline are clear and basic standards slipping away. This is not the Wolverhampton people in my age bracket grew up in, and it should not be the standard we accept for the next generation.\n\nWe need a fresh start!\n\nA council that puts local people first and focuses on the basics, like clean streets, reliable services, and responsible spending.\n\nIf elected, I will be present and accountable. We all want better services, but Labour's £900m debt makes that impossible. Every tax hike just pays interest, not for our roads or care. Let’s stop ‘managing’ debt and start building a city that works.","url":"\"https://sarp.dayanik.co.uk\"","bd":"1957"},{"n":"Prabhjot Kaur Saini","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":349,"r":4,"e"